---
import WorkDetail from '@pt/layouts/WorkDetail.astro'
---

<WorkDetail
  title="App Popular"
  company="Banco Popular Dominicano"
  period="2023 – Present"
  role="Tech Lead"
  category="Finance · iOS & Android"
  stack={['SwiftUI', 'Kotlin', 'iOS', 'Android', 'Agile', 'CI/CD']}
>
  <div class="mb-10">
    <p class="mb-4 font-mono text-[10px] tracking-widest text-[#c9873a] uppercase">Overview</p>
    <p class="mb-4 text-[15px] leading-[1.9] font-light text-white/60">
      App Popular is Banco Popular Dominicano's flagship mobile app — one of the most widely used banking platforms in
      the Dominican Republic. The app gives clients full control of their finances from their phone, eliminating the
      need to visit a branch for everyday banking needs.
    </p>
    <p class="text-[15px] leading-[1.9] font-light text-white/60">
      Clients can check balances, move money, make every type of transaction and reclamation, and manage their account
      configurations — all through a secure, stable mobile experience on both iOS and Android.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10">
    <p class="mb-4 font-mono text-[10px] tracking-widest text-[#c9873a] uppercase">My Role</p>
    <p class="mb-4 text-[15px] leading-[1.9] font-light text-white/60">
      As Tech Lead of an Agile team, I'm involved in the full software lifecycle of every feature we ship.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-4 space-y-3">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="mt-2 h-1 w-1 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-[#c9873a]"></span><p
          class="text-sm leading-relaxed font-light text-white/50"
        >
          Define and scope features based on product and business needs, producing technical documentation that
          minimizes risk before development begins.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="mt-2 h-1 w-1 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-[#c9873a]"></span><p
          class="text-sm leading-relaxed font-light text-white/50"
        >
          Design the data architecture required for each feature, aligned with client needs and backend capabilities.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="mt-2 h-1 w-1 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-[#c9873a]"></span><p
          class="text-sm leading-relaxed font-light text-white/50"
        >
          Participate in UX/UI decisions based on current backend structure, ensuring what gets designed can actually be
          built.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="mt-2 h-1 w-1 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-[#c9873a]"></span><p
          class="text-sm leading-relaxed font-light text-white/50"
        >
          Track features from conception through backend service readiness, with all security controls in place.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="mt-2 h-1 w-1 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-[#c9873a]"></span><p
          class="text-sm leading-relaxed font-light text-white/50"
        >
          Own deployment across Development, QA, and Production environments.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10">
    <p class="mb-4 font-mono text-[10px] tracking-widest text-[#c9873a] uppercase">Featured — Toke</p>
    <p class="text-[15px] leading-[1.9] font-light text-white/60">
      Toke is a payment infrastructure feature launched within App Popular to transform financial inclusion across the
      Dominican Republic. I contributed to the architecture design, security controls, and the full deployment pipeline
      that brought it to production.
    </p>
  </div>
</WorkDetail>
